tldr: The user requested an evaluation of the codebase for database and admin
  dashboard implementation. The plan involved adding a database for
  questionnaire responses, a simple password-protected admin dashboard with CSV
  export, and authentication middleware. The implementation was completed and
  tested, including a simplification of the authentication system using Next.js
  middleware.
overview: The user's intent was to add database functionality and an admin
  dashboard to a sleep questionnaire application as per a Statement of Work. The
  approach involved updating the Prisma schema to store questionnaire responses,
  creating API endpoints for saving and retrieving data (including CSV export),
  and building a simple admin dashboard. Authentication was initially
  implemented with custom session management but was later streamlined using
  Next.js middleware for route protection and a basic cookie-based session. Key
  decisions included using NeonDB for PostgreSQL and a single admin password for
  simplicity. During testing, a form submission issue was identified and
  resolved by ensuring the form was properly submitted to the API. The database,
  API, and dashboard functionalities were successfully verified.
